commit.message:
Fix ODR violation in pathing code

PathAI.cc and Strategic_Pathing.cc both had global
definitions of the types path_t and trail_t. Fixed
by placing the strategic variants in a new namespace.

This commit also removes some old crud from the header.

commit.message:
Fix crash in HandleTextInput()

This function still tried to handle input even when there
was no active input field, for example after calling
DisableAllTextFields(), which could lead to a access
violation when trying to dereference a NULL gpActive
pointer.

Minor cleanup of item creation code

commit.message: Remove TESTFOREIGNFONTS completely

Unbreak inventory slot mouse callbacks

Moving function objects multiple times in a loop ist just
plain stupid; this broke switching inventory items around.

Prevent integer overflow when damaging items

Doing massive damage to an enemy, for example using the
alt+o cheat, could lead to an item's status getting out
of range.

Reduce CPU usage of the main menu screen

Due to some leftovers from really ancient debug code which
used the main menu screen to test the display of foreign
language fonts, the main menu screen redrew its buttons
every game loop. The result was that the game required a
ridicously high number of CPU cycles to render a static
image.

Minor cleanup of item creation code

 Fix off-by-one crash in CycleItemDescriptionItem (cheats only)
 Add warning about invalid status value to CreateItem
 Address some clangd complaints about copying MOUSE_CALLBACKs

commit.message:
Use smart pointers to manage ZStripInfo structs

This removes some boilerplate cleanup code.

Fix bug in InternalTacticalRemoveSoldier panel logic

We can have a non-null gpSMCurrentMerc even when the current
screen is not the game screen. Calling SetCurrentInterfacePanel()
in that situation leads to all the interface elements of the
panel being created, so you could for example end up with a
Change Squad button on the main menu screen.
